column2: So, what is the reason to say hello world. I mean, why it is world but not anything else like "hello C++" or "hello python"? This is indeed an important question isn't it! I wrote my first hello world program like 3 years ago yeah I am sure it was a night of 2022. I was living in Shanghai and we were not allowed to get out of our door due to that COVID-19. I spent time learning python for the very first time reading a stupid book.
Learn more algorithm and do more leetcode and you got job?
